  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> For \\( 2x^2 + 12x + 5 \\), factoring gives \\( 2(x^2 + 6x + 5) \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Only the \\( x \\)-terms are factored: \\( 2(x^2 + 6x) + 5 \\). A weak answer drags the constant inside; a strong answer keeps \\( +5 \\) outside and finishes \\( 2(x+3)^2 - 13 \\).</p>",
