  "readingTitle": "explain — State the quotient AND the remainder",
  "reading": "<p>The 2023 examiners reported that candidates who divided correctly still lost the final mark by <strong>not identifying the quotient</strong>, or by <strong>giving the remainder as a fraction</strong>.</p><p><strong>0 marks lost:</strong> a page of correct working but no stated answer, or \"remainder \\( = \\frac{-6}{x-3} \\)\".</p><p><strong>Full marks:</strong> \"Quotient \\( = x^2 + 2x + 3 \\), Remainder \\( = -6 \\)\" — both labelled, the remainder a number.</p>",
