  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> For \\( x_{n+1} = 5x_n \\) with \\( x_1 = 2 \\), writing \\( x_2 = 2 + 5 = 7 \\).</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> The rule multiplies, it does not add. A weak answer treats \\( 5x_n \\) as \\( x_n + 5 \\); a strong answer writes \\( x_2 = 5 \\times 2 = 10 \\).</p>",
